{{Infobox language |name=Boanarí |nativename= |states= |region= |ethnicity= |extinct=? |ref= |familycolor=American |fam1=[[Cariban languages|Cariban]] |fam2=Atruahí? |iso3=none |glotto=bona1255 |glottorefname=Bonari }}
'''Boanarí''' (Bonari) is an extinct and poorly attested [[Cariban language]]. Kaufman (2007) placed it in his Atruahí branch.
