949781/Punch-and-Judy-around-the-world.html|agency=The Telegraph|date=11 June 2015}}</ref> * [[Elizabeth II|The Queen]] and the [[British Royal Family|Royal Family]].<ref name="Icons"/> * [[Received Pronunciation]], or the Queen's English.<ref name="Icons"/> * The [[Red Arrows]].<ref name="Icons"/> * Royal Mail [[pillar box|red pillar box]].<ref>[http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2479115/How-Royal-Mail-builds-Britains-iconic-letter-boxes.html#ixzz3IDFUe7u2 "From pillar to post: How Royal Mail builds Britain's letter boxes - and why they look exactly the same now as they did 160 years ago"]. Daily Mail. Retrieved 5 November 2014</ref> * The [[red telephone box]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Odone|first=Cristina|title=The trashing of the iconic red phone box is one bad call|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/comment/9921689/The-trashing-of-the-iconic-red-phone-box-is-one-bad-call.html|newspaper=Telegraph|date=11 March 2013}}</ref> * The red [[AEC Routemaster]] double-decker bus.<ref name="Icons"/> * [[William Shakespeare]] (1564-1616).<ref name="Icons"/> * [[Stonehenge]].<ref name="Icons"/> * The [[Sunday roast]].<ref name="Icons"/> * The [[Tower of London]].<ref name="Icons"/> * The [[Union Flag]].<ref name="Icons"/> * [[Whisky]].<ref name="Scotsman"/>
